key to our investment process our team focuses on the consumer tmt industrials and healthcare sectors and invests in companies across all equity stages hillhouse manages capital for institutional clients such as university endowments foundations sovereign wealth funds pensions and family offices our people zhang lei founder  ceo mr zhang lei is the founder and ceo of hillhouse capital group prior to founding hillhouse mr zhang worked with the yale endowment and a global emerging market fund covering south africa southeast asia and china mr zhang earned an mba and ma in international relations from yale university and a ba in economics from renmin university of chinamr zhang is a trustee of yale university and is also vice chairman and trustee of the board at renmin university he is the founder and chairman of gaoli academy of renmin university which he established in  in addition mr zhang is the chair of the yale asia development council full profile      hillhouse capital group all rights reserved use of this website is governed by the terms of use the content contained on this site is provided to users as is without any express or implied warranty portfolio companies  hillhouse capital group about us portfolio companies news since  hillhouse has invested in many leading companies in their respective industries below are selected portfolio companies     hillhouse capital group all rights reserved use of this website is governed by the terms of use the content contained on this site is provided to users as is without any express or implied warranty news  hillhouse capital group about us portfolio companies news choose to be a friend of time june   on june rd hillhouse’s founder lei zhang gave the commencement speech to the graduating class of  at renmin university lei zhangs lecture at columbia business school hillhouse capital july    zong z peng  market folly below are notes from hillhouse capitals lei zhangs lecture at columbia business school courtesy of zong z peng original reference original reference a decade later former yio intern now manages billions april    larry milstein  yale daily news “it is no coincidence that zhang named his firm in honor of the street that runs through yale’s campus just three years after zhang graduated the university became one of his earliest backers “seeding”  million in capital when zhang first solicited investments” the chinese billionaire zhang lei spins research into investment gold april    alexandra stevenson  the newyork times “with an  billion war chest he is one of china’s richest investors yet on a recent trip to san francisco zhang lei and his entourage crammed into a threebedroom house in the mission district rented through airbnb” original reference original reference cardekhocom raised usd  million january    cardekho team  cardekhocom jaipur cardekhocom the flagship portal of girnarsoft announced the closure of second round of funding with a raise of usd  million the funding was led by hillhouse capital with participation from tybourne capital and sequoia capital the single transaction funding was concluded early this week hillhouse capital leads  mln round for saltside january    iris dorbian  pe hub saltside technologies has raised  million in funding hillhouse capital led the round with participation from brummer  partners and investment ab kinnevik based in sweden saltside runs online classifieds platforms in bangladesh sri lanka and ghana original reference original reference mayo clinic signs joint venture agreement with hillhouse capital group january    brian kilen  mayo clinic today mayo clinic announced it has entered into a joint venture agreement with hillhouse capital to advance the quality of health care in china by combining mayo clinic’s patient care medical research and education with hillhouse’s china expertise and healthcare industry partnerships the collaboration establishes a new company to improve health care delivery and efficiency in china how do you invest in a changing china november   yale insights lei zhang ’ has been one of the most successful investors in china during a time of unprecedented change in a conversation with yale’s stephen roach he talked about rapid shifts in china’s business and culture the birth of a consumer class the chinese innovation model and the outmoded views of the country that remain prevalent in the west original reference original reference a single ladle from a flowing stream zhang lei  perspectives on the long term  fclt having partners who are long term themselves gives me freedom to focus on what i love which is working with exceptional entrepreneurs to build businesses that optimize for the next ten years rather than the next quarter zhang lei has lunch with the ft june    henny sender  financial times the billionaire chinese financier was among the first to see the potential in homegrown internet companies he talks about a career that began when he rented out comics at the age of seven original reference original reference hillhouse’s zhang says now one of best times to invest in china june    bei hu  bloomberg now is one of the best times to invest in china in  years as a slowing economy reduces overcapacity and forces companies to focus on generating free cash flow said zhang lei founder of yale universitybacked hillhouse capital management ltd original reference     hillhouse capital group all rights reserved use of this website is governed by the terms of use the content contained on this site is provided to users as is without any express or implied warranty hillhouse capital group  wikipedia hillhouse capital group from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search hillhouse capital group type private industry hedge fund private equity venture capital founded   years ago  founder lei zhang website wwwhillhousecapcom hillhouse capital group “hillhouse” is an investment management firm founded by zhang lei in  with us million in seed capital from the yale endowment hillhouse manages over us billion as of january citation needed and is known for its avoidance of publicity hillhouse manages capital for institutional clients such as university endowments foundations sovereign wealth funds pension funds and family offices hillhouse is a longterm fundamental researchdriven equity investor hillhouse focuses on the consumer tmt industrials and healthcare sectors and invests in companies across all equity stages hillhouse has over  investment professionals across its offices in beijing hong kong and singapore it invests globally with a particular focus on asia contents  history  performance  notable investments  joint ventures  investment philosophy  notable investors  references  external links historyedit zhang lei founded hillhouse capital group in june  the company is named after an avenue in new haven one block from where the yale investment office was previously located zhang used an initial  million which he received from yale through david swensen yale’s chief investment officer to begin hillhouse an additional  million soon followed according to the financial times zhang built hillhouse by being one of the first investment firms to back mainland china’s burgeoning internet sector including investing in tencent holdings ltd which is one of china’s most valuable internet companies today hillhouse was also one of the first firms to invest in jdcom the ecommerce giant performanceedit hillhouse has achieved investment returns of up to  annualized from inception until  even in spite of a  drop in  making hillhouse among the most profitable funds of its size in the world and the leading fund in asia in  returns had reportedly dropped to over  owing to its low profile but high performance founder zhang lei and hillhouse have been likened to stephen mandel and lone pine capital notable investmentsedit tencent holdings ltd some of the original  million provided from yale was invested in tencent holidings in  it was hillhouse’s earliest investment and one of their most profitable jdcom hillhouse was also an early investor in jdcom at the time of the listing of jdcom on nasdaq in may  the company was valued at  billion hillhouse’s original  million investment was at the time of the ipo valued at  billion blue moon hillhouse invested in blue moon a liquid detergent maker in  as its only outside institutional investor in  blue moon was ranked  in the china brand power index published by ministry of industry and information technology the market share of its liquid detergent has been ranked  in china for the past five consecutive years joint venturesedit hillhouse established an exclusive joint venture focused on china with the us healthcare provider mayo clinic hillhouse will work with the mayo organization to expand its influence in china hillhouse and mayo celebrated the establishment of this joint venture in january  with a healthcare conference in beijing where healthcare industry ceos regulators and academics participated in a discussion about the future of healthcare in china investment philosophyedit henny sender discussed zhang’s investment philosophy in an article published in the financial times according to sender “zhang sees himself as the product of both east and west” hillhouse does deep and fundamental research on industries and business models and applies the value investing philosophy in local contexts while investing in different geographies according to sender zhang often brings together leaders of private companies particularly portfolio companies for informal discussions he believes it is beneficial for executives to learn from one another when leaders of jdcom met with leaders from a hypermarket company zhang said “etailers learn how offline companies think and retailers learn how ecommerce companies think” zhang also believes that china’s business model is better suited to emerging markets and is therefore bringing that model to developing nations in asia in indonesia hillhouse launched a joint venture between mobile messaging platform wechat and indonesia’s giant communications and media conglomerate global mediacom “indonesia is now like china some years ago” commented zhang sender also explains that zhang’s investment philosophy is comparable to that of warren buffett which is to buy and hold “in a world of speculators zhang’s philosophy stands out” insider monkey pointed out that some of hillhouse’s investment decisions could be classified as contrarian although they do maintain a considerable number of mainstream investments as well notable investorsedit under a plan reported in august  for stanford university to invest about  million with hillhouse the group will be investing money for at least six of the  wealthiest universities in the us referencesedit  a b c d e f sender henny  june  zhang lei has lunch with the ft financial times retrieved  march    nadeem m  january  hillhouse capital management cuts passive stake insider monkey retrieved  march    a b c lowprofile beijing fund with envious record subscription only ftcom january   partially retrieved   a b hu bei  january  hillhouse capital said to raise  billion private equity fund bloomberg business retrieved  march    investment philosophy hillhouse capital retrieved  march    value investing congress retrieved  march    sender henny  june  zhang lei has lunch with the ft financial times retrieved  april  the fund is named after an avenue in new haven that’s a block from where the yale investment office used to be located   mcenery thornton the  biggest asianbased hedge funds businessinsidercom may   retrieved   zhangvalueinvestingcongresswestpdfdead link valuewalkcom   research  rankings top of the hill institutional investors alphacenveomobilecom summer  retrieved   hillhouse dst and capital today to exit in jdcoms m followon offering china money network  november  retrieved  march    （广州实业有限公司简称 in chinese baikebaidu retrieved  march    mayo and hillhouse capita